(79, 72, '194', 'Wetlands of International Importance (Ramsar Sites) - Area', 'Hectares', 'Wetlands are defined by the convention as: areas of marsh, fen, peatland or water, whether natural or artificial, permanent or temporary, with water that is static or flowing, fresh, brackish or salt, including areas of marine waters, the depth of which at low tide does not exceed six metres.', '#b1aa7c'),
