(169, 168, '613', 'Crude Birth Rate', 'Births per Thousand People', 'Crude birth rate: number  of births over a given period divided by the person-years lived by the population over that period. It is expressed as number of births per 1,000 population.', '#593b9b'),
(170, 168, '247', 'Crude Death Rate', 'Deaths per Thousand People', 'Crude death rate: number  of deaths over a given period divided by the person-years lived by the population over that period. It is expressed as number of deaths per 1,000 population.', '#fe6498'),
(171, 168, '49', 'Fertility', 'Number of Children per Woman', 'The average number of children a hypothetical cohort of women would have at the end of their reproductive period if they were subject during their whole lives to the fertility rates of a given period and if  they were not subject to mortality. It is expressed as children per woman.', '#16a4b3'),
